In PvE, you cannot afford to shout every time your timer reset if you don't have PoM, like casters can't afford to dump all of their power every fight. You and your group have to adjust your power (and endurance) consumption to keep the pulls rolling. <br>
<br>
Generally it is not a good idea to have a skald as a main tank (unfortunately, it seems all low-mid level mids are skalds, SBs, runies or sms, with the occasional zerker heh <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ). While skalds can tank effectively until their late 30ies, they'll be more and more of a healer's mana sponge compared to a shield specced warrior (or thane). And, like you said, you'll need your shouts to keep aggro, adding a lot to downtime. So the real answer to your problem is to get an efficient group rolling, which is not easy with the relative rarity of healers and the understandable lack of lower level warriors.<br>
<br>
Apart from that, MCL is extremely good (and worth the cost at level 1), Serenity is nice (but not necessarily worth the cost, IP is damn expensive ...).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/ugisborne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 117<br> <font color=#ff0000>(9/23/02 3:50:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=331.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> EZboard is starting to piss me off</span><hr size=1> You might want to modify your spec a little. Keep battlesongs at 25 and raise weapon till it's above songs. You get extra damage, and it doesn't take power.<br>
